# Multi-Region Kubernetes Deployment on AWS & GCP

## Overview
This project demonstrates the deployment of a highly available, multi-region Kubernetes cluster on AWS EKS and GCP GKE using Terraform and CI/CD pipelines. It showcases cloud architecture, automation, and observability at scale.

## Tech Stack
- AWS: EKS, VPC, RDS, S3
- GCP: GKE, Cloud SQL, Cloud Storage
- Kubernetes, Helm
- Terraform (IaC)
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions / Jenkins
- Monitoring: Prometheus, Grafana, ELK Stack
- Automation: Python / Bash

## Features
- Multi-region Kubernetes clusters supporting 250+ microservices
- Autoscaling and rolling deployments
- Centralized monitoring and logging
- Automated CI/CD pipelines
- Cost optimization via Terraform best practices

